Before this, Li Tian once asked me a question.

207
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:57,370
He asked if I ever experienced that feeling of not being able to absorb knowledge.

208
00:16:57,370 --> 00:16:58,700
I didn't answer him.

209
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:01,136
I was afraid of hurting his pride

210
00:17:01,136 --> 00:17:03,730
because, honestly, I had never felt that way.

211
00:17:03,730 --> 00:17:07,530
But now...

212
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:09,000
I finally understand it.

213
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:13,680
So now you've gone from a highly capable top student to a less capable good student,

214
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:16,040
and you can't accept it?

215
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:19,260
Not exactly.

216
00:17:23,130 --> 00:17:26,680
It's not that I can't accept being less capable than others.

217
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,630
It's just that...

218
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:33,610
I feel like I could do better.

219
00:17:37,810 --> 00:17:44,680
You know, sculptures like Venus weren't unique in ancient Greece.

220
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:51,190
But only this one that lost its arms became an unsurpassable masterpiece in art history.

221
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:56,770
Because its imperfections spark people's imaginations even more?

222
00:17:56,770 --> 00:17:58,530
Maybe.

223
00:17:58,530 --> 00:18:02,290
But I prefer another interpretation.

224
00:18:04,950 --> 00:18:08,910
There is no such thing as perfection in this world.

225
00:18:08,910 --> 00:18:12,950
To be human is to be flawed.

226
00:18:12,950 --> 00:18:14,290
It's not just you.

227
00:18:14,290 --> 00:18:16,470
Everyone is the same.

228
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:19,800
Oh, by the way, I have something to tell you.

229
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:22,200
I'm transferring to the Literature Department.

230
00:18:23,130 --> 00:18:27,973
Although I don't know whether the path of literature will be bright in the future,

231
00:18:27,973 --> 00:18:32,260
