I've been calling you all day, and you're not answering!

265
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:28,090
What kind of big business do you have now?

266
00:21:28,090 --> 00:21:31,060
I was playing soccer and didn't bring my phone.

267
00:21:31,060 --> 00:21:34,460
You don't look like you've just played soccer.

268
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:38,850
Well, maybe it's just because I was born naturally good-looking.

269
00:21:38,850 --> 00:21:42,150
Don't pretend. I can smell your shampoo.

270
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:50,014
What's wrong with you?

271
00:21:50,014 --> 00:21:52,140
Did you get your heart broken?

272
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:54,240
What?

273
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,300
You think I'm the type to get heartbroken?

274
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:58,810
Oh yeah, now you're a star in the Computer Science Department.

275
00:21:58,810 --> 00:22:00,450
It's different from before.

276
00:22:00,450 --> 00:22:02,050
I'm in high demand now.

277
00:22:02,050 --> 00:22:03,580
Exactly.

278
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:06,645
I heard about the pink rose thing.

279
00:22:06,645 --> 00:22:08,800
Did someone confess to you?

280
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:12,510
I turned her down.

281
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:15,280
Why?

282
00:22:16,180 --> 00:22:20,210
Don't you think she looks a bit like our high school English teacher?

283
00:22:20,210 --> 00:22:22,580
Does she? Du Wei is quite pretty, though.

284
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:27,450
I'm not talking about her looks. It's her vibe.

285
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:31,340
She always seems smiley, but deep down, she's super serious.

286
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:35,400
I'm scared I'd dream about her forcing me to finish an English practice set.

287
00:22:36,460 --> 00:22:38,840
You're nuts.

288
00:22:39,790 --> 00:22:42,840
Speaking of that, why did you go for Tian Chi?

289
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,810
He seems like such a boring guy.

290
00:22:44,810 --> 00:22:46,450
I just thought I'd give it a try.

291
00:22:46,450 --> 00:22:50,290
You never know what you like until you try.

292
00:22:50,290 --> 00:22:52,900
If you wanted to try it, did it have to be him?

293
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:55,620
If you wanted to try dating a top student, you could've picked Cong.

294
00:22:55,620 --> 00:22:57,870
Are you out of your mind?

295
00:23:00,020 --> 00:23:01,640
- You're mad. 
 - No, I'm not.

296
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,250
- You're mad. 
 - I'm not!

297
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:05,550
Definitely mad.

298
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:09,760
I brought you a lot of snacks.

299
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:11,180
Come on, I'm an adult now.

300
00:23:11,180 --> 00:23:12,460
I don't eat these.

301
00:23:12,460 --> 00:23:14,880
I got you a ton of chips!

302
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:17,150
Why is there no Little Raccoon's crunchy noodles?

303
00:23:17,150 --> 00:23:20,250
They don't sell them at the campus store anymore.

304
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:26,770
The favorite restaurants close down.

305
00:23:26,770 --> 00:23:28,980
The favorite snacks disappear.

306
00:23:28,980 --> 00:23:31,210
Why does this happen?

307
00:23:36,390 --> 00:23:38,260
You can try new snacks.

308
00:23:38,260 --> 00:23:40,350
This one's really good.

309
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:49,150
How is it? Is it good?

310
00:23:49,150 --> 00:23:50,310
It's good.

311
00:23:50,310 --> 00:23:52,310
It tastes good.

312
00:23:52,870 --> 00:23:57,250
But some things just can't be replaced.

313
00:23:58,220 --> 00:23:59,830
Right?

314
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:06,730
Yeah.

315
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:13,560
If you like it, I'll buy you another pack next time.

316
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:15,237
Just one pack?

317
00:24:15,237 --> 00:24:16,350
One pack isn't enough?

318
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:18,260
You're so stingy.

319
00:24:18,260 --> 00:24:19,630
You say I'm stingy?

320
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:22,100
Remember back in high school when we got robbed?

321
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:24,700
You bought only one can of Jianlibao and shared it with Song Cong,

322
00:24:24,700 --> 00:24:26,350
but you didn't let me drink.

323
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,980
You still remember such a trivial thing?

324
00:24:27,980 --> 00:24:29,550
Of course I do. I hold grudges.

325
00:24:29,550 --> 00:24:33,070
Do you remember the agriculture study? I gave you everything I had.

326
00:24:33,070 --> 00:24:34,070
Lies!

327
00:24:34,070 --> 00:24:37,660
You clearly gave half of it to Song Cong.

328
00:24:37,660 --> 00:24:39,160
- You forgot? 
 - Did I?

329
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,790
- You really don't remember? 
 - I don't think so.

330
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:42,740
- You did! Don't try to weasel out of it. 
 - No way.

331
00:24:42,740 --> 00:24:45,000
I swear I gave it all to you.

332
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,700
Hold this for me.

333
00:24:50,740 --> 00:24:52,420
Oh no!

334
00:24:53,260 --> 00:24:54,780
   

335
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:57,350
 Hello, Huan Er. 

336
00:24:57,350 --> 00:24:59,680
Sorry, are you still there?

337
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:00,989
Are you already here?

338
00:25:00,989 --> 00:25:02,780
 I'm sorry. 

339
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:07,140
How about we go there another day?

340
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:10,740
 - All right.  
 - Sorry.

341
00:25:10,740 --> 00:25:13,220
Rest early.

342
00:25:14,260 --> 00:25:15,790
Okay.

343
00:25:15,790 --> 00:25:17,310
 Bye. 

344
00:25:26,620 --> 00:25:29,360
   

345
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:39,560
Well... I'm heading back.

346
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,480
They are about to rest now.

347
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:45,681
What about you?

348
00:25:45,681 --> 00:25:47,940
I'll just stay here for a bit.

349
00:26:00,980 --> 00:26:02,600
Bye.

350
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:12,530
Jing Xi Chi, what are you doing?

351
00:26:21,870 --> 00:26:23,980
Tian Chi...

352
00:26:24,790 --> 00:26:26,790
why are you here?

353
00:26:26,790 --> 00:26:33,940
Huan Er, actually, today I do have something I wanted to tell you.

354
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:36,560
I...

355
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,958
I also have something to tell you.

356
00:26:38,958 --> 00:26:40,901
Let me finish first.

357
00:26:40,901 --> 00:26:45,250
I'm afraid that if I don't say it now, I won't get another chance.

358
00:26:50,460 --> 00:26:53,940
I'm not good with words,

359
00:26:54,700 --> 00:26:58,590
but for some reason, every time I see you,

360
00:26:58,590 --> 00:27:04,120
I become nervous, which makes me unable to say what I want.

361
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:07,830
Even when I do, it never comes out right.

362
00:27:07,830 --> 00:27:13,150
So, whenever we part, I regret it,

363
00:27:14,420 --> 00:27:16,890
thinking I didn't do enough.

364
00:27:20,780 --> 00:27:26,520
I always believed that feelings should happen naturally.

365
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:29,100
I think there's a long way to go,

366
00:27:29,100 --> 00:27:33,540
and as time passes, the two people will eventually become closer.

367
00:27:35,060 --> 00:27:37,340
But I realized I was wrong.

368
00:27:40,580 --> 00:27:45,910
I know there is someone very important in your heart.

369
00:27:47,100 --> 00:27:51,290
But unfortunately, that person isn't me.

370
00:28:03,990 --> 00:28:08,570
I'm sorry, Tian Chi.

371
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:12,460
Maybe you're right.

372
00:28:13,670 --> 00:28:19,680
Right now, I really can't like anyone else.

373
00:28:25,150 --> 00:28:29,640
I should return this book to you.

374
00:28:30,390 --> 00:28:34,390
Things that don't belong to me shouldn't be kept.

375
00:28:36,230 --> 00:28:40,740
I also hope you find your own happiness.

376
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:56,480
I wish you happiness, too.

377
00:28:57,190 --> 00:28:58,810
Sincerely.

378
00:29:02,430 --> 00:29:04,020
Then...

379
00:29:04,020 --> 00:29:05,970
I'll get going now.

380
00:29:48,630 --> 00:29:50,800
You seem to be in a good mood.

381
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:53,540
What happened? Did Tian Chi confess to you?

382
00:29:53,540 --> 00:29:55,100
Yeah.

383
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:59,530
- You're not single anymore— 
 - I turned him down.

384
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:02,540
I knew it.

385
00:30:02,540 --> 00:30:03,840
Why?

386
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:06,990
He's such a great guy. Why don't you like him?

387
00:30:06,990 --> 00:30:12,950
Li said not to ask why you love someone or why you don't.

388
00:30:12,950 --> 00:30:14,780
Good girl.

389
00:30:15,870 --> 00:30:18,150
What does that mean?

390
00:30:18,150 --> 00:30:19,880
I know this one!

391
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:21,580
In White Horse Neighs in the Western Wind,

392
00:30:21,580 --> 00:30:27,050
Li Wen Xiu mentions: "There are many wonderful things.

393
00:30:27,050 --> 00:30:30,630
But I just don't like them."

394
00:30:31,190 --> 00:30:35,200
 But some things just can't be replaced. 

395
00:30:36,060 --> 00:30:37,770
 Right? 

396
00:30:42,630 --> 00:30:43,950
 Yeah. 

397
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:01,630
Come on.

398
00:31:01,630 --> 00:31:03,370
Try this cake.

399
00:31:03,370 --> 00:31:07,500
I specifically bought two flavors. Both are your favorites. Try them.

400
00:31:08,580 --> 00:31:13,300
I tell you, I knew you would reject Tian Chi.

401
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:16,640
Why are you so sure that I'd turn him down?

402
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:19,890
Think about this. Cong is such an outstanding guy,

403
00:31:19,890 --> 00:31:21,950
and you already rejected him.

404
00:31:21,950 --> 00:31:24,920
Compared to Song, Tian Chi is still far away.

405
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:28,260
Even if you're dying to fall in love, you shouldn't settle, right?

406
00:31:28,260 --> 00:31:30,540
Can you stop bringing up Cong?

407
00:31:30,540 --> 00:31:31,950
You're so petty.

408
00:31:31,950 --> 00:31:33,230
I'm not petty.

409
00:31:33,230 --> 00:31:35,570
I'm just curious.

410
00:31:39,990 --> 00:31:43,780
You've turned down two guys already.

411
00:31:43,780 --> 00:31:46,630
So, what kind of person do you actually like?

412
00:31:46,630 --> 00:31:52,470
Do you have a specific description of him in your mind?

413
00:31:52,470 --> 00:31:58,430
Like his hair length, his personality, or his...

414
00:31:58,430 --> 00:32:01,950
Why do you even want to know that?

415
00:32:03,695 --> 00:32:07,040
I just see you single all the time, and it shouldn't be like that.

416
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:11,720
I don't have an ideal type.

417
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:15,640
But don't girls usually love fantasizing about this?

418
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:18,230
I'm not an ordinary girl.

419
00:32:26,300 --> 00:32:30,190
 Huan Er, Song Cong and I are thinking of visiting during the break. 

420
00:32:30,190 --> 00:32:32,300
- What's going on? 
 - Qi Qi just told me

421
00:32:32,300 --> 00:32:35,430
that she and Cong are coming to visit us in a few days.

422
00:32:36,470 --> 00:32:38,580
- The two of them? 
 - Yeah.

423
00:32:38,580 --> 00:32:40,330
Coming to visit us?

424
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:45,660
Do you want to eat this cake? If not, I'll have it.

425
00:32:45,660 --> 00:32:46,920
You aren't curious at all.

426
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,530
- Yeah. 
 - The two of them...

427
00:32:48,530 --> 00:32:50,130
Yeah, so?

428
00:32:50,130 --> 00:32:52,890
Stop eating! They've known each other since high school.

429
00:32:52,890 --> 00:32:54,880
And now, they're finally...

430
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:56,290
Aren't you curious about its flavor?

431
00:32:56,290 --> 00:32:58,330
Not really.

432
00:32:58,330 --> 00:32:59,640
I'll try this one instead.

433
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:01,100
Don't guys usually not like sweets?

434
00:33:01,100 --> 00:33:02,320
Well, I'm not an ordinary guy.

435
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:04,580
These are for me, aren't they?

436
00:33:05,540 --> 00:33:07,440
Drink your coffee.

437
00:33:13,780 --> 00:33:16,520
 - I'll carry it. 
 - It's fine. I can carry it. 

438
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:20,020
Cong, what a lame place you found! It's so foggy.

439
00:33:20,020 --> 00:33:21,990
That's just how it is in the mountain.

440
00:33:21,990 --> 00:33:24,490
Once the sun comes up, it'll clear.

441
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:30,430
Later, in front of Song Cong, don't mention anything about grades or rankings.

442
00:33:30,430 --> 00:33:33,780
From what I know about him, he's just used to being at the top.

443
00:33:33,780 --> 00:33:36,660
He can't bear a sudden drop in grades.

444
00:33:38,470 --> 00:33:42,430
Since love can cure everything, why not match him up with someone?

445
00:33:42,430 --> 00:33:43,820
So it takes his mind off things.

446
00:33:43,820 --> 00:33:46,190
Wow, your little brain is so smart.

447
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:48,020
Yeah.

448
00:33:49,150 --> 00:33:50,910
Hello, I've reserved two rooms.

449
00:33:50,910 --> 00:33:53,600
- Please wait a moment. 
 - All right. Thank you.

450
00:34:00,260 --> 00:34:02,220
- Wow, he's so handsome. 
 - He's your cup of tea.

451
00:34:02,220 --> 00:34:04,300
Isn't he your type?

452
00:34:14,220 --> 00:34:17,180
What's your relationship with him now?

453
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:18,950
What do you mean?

454
00:34:18,950 --> 00:34:22,910
I saw him carrying your luggage so naturally.

455
00:34:22,910 --> 00:34:24,830
I thought you two were already...

456
00:34:24,830 --> 00:34:26,950
It's the same as before.

457
00:34:26,950 --> 00:34:29,680
I help him, he helps me.

458
00:34:30,700 --> 00:34:33,390
But I saw Cong carrying your luggage too.

459
00:34:33,390 --> 00:34:35,660
How's that going between you two?

460
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:45,700
Didn't you notice? He only did that because Jing Xi Chi helped you first.

461
00:34:45,700 --> 00:34:47,740
Forget about that. Let's talk about something pleasant.

462
00:34:47,740 --> 00:34:50,440
I switched my major from Law to Chinese Literature.

463
00:34:50,440 --> 00:34:53,430
Really? That's great.

464
00:34:53,430 --> 00:34:55,180
I'm really happy now.

465
00:34:55,180 --> 00:34:58,700
I feel like my world suddenly opened up.

466
00:34:58,700 --> 00:35:01,310
Maybe because I opened up too.

467
00:35:01,310 --> 00:35:08,660
So now, I also want to help Song Cong get out of his slump as well.

468
00:35:08,660 --> 00:35:09,830
Really?

469
00:35:09,830 --> 00:35:12,180
I don't think it's that simple.

470
00:35:14,430 --> 00:35:16,140
It's not?

471
00:35:16,140 --> 00:35:17,790
No, it isn't.

472
00:35:18,540 --> 00:35:21,750
How is everything going between you and Qi Qi?

473
00:35:21,750 --> 00:35:23,220
What do you mean?

474
00:35:23,220 --> 00:35:26,150
Don't play dumb. You know what I mean.

475
00:35:29,220 --> 00:35:32,220
I think Qi Qi is different now,

476
00:35:33,140 --> 00:35:35,220
but I can't quite say how.

477
00:35:36,220 --> 00:35:39,640
What about you? How's everything between you and Chen Huan Er?

478
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:42,470
What do you mean?

479
00:35:42,470 --> 00:35:44,600
Don't play dumb.

480
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,280
When are you going to confess?

481
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:49,055
I've known for a long time that you like her.

482
00:35:49,055 --> 00:35:51,270
How did you figure that out?

483
00:35:51,270 --> 00:35:53,100
Instinct.

484
00:35:58,470 --> 00:36:01,600
Do you mind that I used to like Chen Huan Er?

485
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:06,910
When I first found out, of course I did.

486
00:36:06,910 --> 00:36:10,040
But I don't care anymore because it's been so long already.

487
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:14,232
Do you still like her?

488
00:36:14,232 --> 00:36:15,890
Are you crazy?

489
00:36:16,990 --> 00:36:19,900
If you like her, why don't you confess?

490
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:26,774
I'm afraid that if I fail, we won't even be friends anymore.

491
00:36:26,774 --> 00:36:28,579
See, weren't the two of you just like that?

492
00:36:28,579 --> 00:36:30,890
Didn't you start talking less afterward?

493
00:36:32,620 --> 00:36:36,640
I didn't think that far ahead back then.

494
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:41,520
So you care about your relationship with Chen Huan Er more than I did.

495
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:43,660
Hello, your check-in is complete.

496
00:36:43,660 --> 00:36:45,660
Thank you.

497
00:36:45,660 --> 00:36:48,720
- It's done? 
 - Let's go. It's done.

498
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:51,590
- Where's your suitcase? 
 - It's there.

499
00:36:55,350 --> 00:36:57,220
Jing Xi Chi.

500
00:36:58,180 --> 00:36:59,840
What's up?

501
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,728
What were you doing?

502
00:37:01,728 --> 00:37:03,790
Go straight to the point.

503
00:37:03,790 --> 00:37:06,020
We need to figure out a way to get them to leave first

504
00:37:06,020 --> 00:37:08,430
so they can spend time with each other.

505
00:37:08,430 --> 00:37:10,710
How is this possible?

506
00:37:12,540 --> 00:37:14,820
Let's think of some good ideas.

507
00:37:21,620 --> 00:37:23,500
I've got it!

508
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:27,439
What are you doing? I don't have time for this right now.

509
00:37:27,439 --> 00:37:28,500
I figured out a way!

510
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:30,270
What way?

511
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:33,290
Are you crazy, Chen Huan Er?

512
00:37:36,470 --> 00:37:40,140
Help!

513
00:37:40,140 --> 00:37:43,880
Help!

514
00:37:43,880 --> 00:37:45,660
Shout with me! Scream!

515
00:37:45,660 --> 00:37:46,870
You can do it on your own.

516
00:37:46,870 --> 00:37:48,140
Shout with me!

517
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:49,700
Hurry!

518
00:37:49,700 --> 00:37:51,790
What's wrong with this?

519
00:37:51,790 --> 00:37:55,470
- Why is the water so strong? 
 - It's spraying everywhere!

520
00:37:55,470 --> 00:37:58,470
 - My clothes are soaked! 
 - Help! 

521
00:37:58,470 --> 00:37:59,910
 Why is the water so strong? 

522
00:37:59,910 --> 00:38:01,750
 Let me check it. 

523
00:38:01,750 --> 00:38:04,270
They're coming. Faster!

524
00:38:04,270 --> 00:38:05,460
Come.

525
00:38:10,080 --> 00:38:11,660
- What happened? 
 - What's wrong?

526
00:38:11,660 --> 00:38:12,830
Why are you all soaked?

527
00:38:12,830 --> 00:38:15,320
The shower head broke, and we got sprayed all over.

528
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:17,060
- Yeah. 
 - Should we switch rooms?

529
00:38:17,060 --> 00:38:18,580
